2\%) remained in hospital. The median postdischarge follow-up time was 4.4 days ({IQR}, 2.2-9.3). A total of 45 patients (2.2\%) were readmitted during the study period. The median time to readmission was 3 days ({IQR}, 1.0-4.5) for readmitted patients. Among the 3066 patients who remained hospitalized at the final study follow-up date (median age, 65 years [{IQR}, 54-75]), the median follow-up at time of censoring was 4.5 days ({IQR}, 2.4-8.1).This case series provides characteristics and early outcomes of sequentially hospitalized patients with confirmed {COVID}-19 in the New York City area.},
