s started during hospital admission for myocardial infarction (0.64, 0.44 to 0.94; P=0.02). {CONCLUSIONS}: The use of beta blockers started either at the time of hospital admission for myocardial infarction or before a myocardial infarction is associated with improved survival after myocardial infarction in patients with {COPD}. {REGISTRATION}: {NCT}01335672.},
