tly lower in the statin-{ARB} cohort (adjusted {HR} 0.69, 95\% {CI} 0.59-0.81). {CONCLUSION}: A {MACCE} was less likely to occur in patients who received a statin-{ARB} than in those who received a statin-{ACEI}. Similar trends were seen in cardiovascular mortality and the occurrence of recurrent {MI} but not stroke. The availability of statin-{ARB} fixed-dose combinations may have contributed to the improved outcomes in the statin-{ARB} cohort by reducing pill burden and improving medication adherence. Further research is warranted to validate our findings and to address whether a particular statin-{ARB} combination is more effective than other combinations.},
