al samples. Using simulated and experimental data, we demonstrate novel probability-based scores that adjust for the compositional nature of relative abundance data to accurately quantify taxon-level {IgA} binding. All scoring approaches are made available in the {IgAScores} R package. These methods should improve the generation and interpretation of {IgA}-Seq datasets and could be applied to study other immunoglobulins and sample types. [{MediaObject} not available: see fulltext.]},
