	abstract = {Background: Women are at greater risk of developing resistant hypertension ({RH}) than men, yet scarce data exist on {RH}-associated outcomes in women. We aimed to determine all-cause mortality risk associated with apparent {RH} ({aRH}) among women across the spectrum of underlying coronary disease.

